transcripts.text: Even if Biden manages to win, he's screwed.  Hi, I'm Scott Ott, and this is Right Angle with Bill Whittle and Stephen Green.  And gentlemen, I hate to do two stories in one week that both come out of Politico, but this is another one.  Another think piece in the wake of the election that continues to linger on, the vote counting continuing in multiple states and across the country.  And the upshot of the story, gentlemen, is that no matter who wins the election, if it The Democrats, who were expecting to grow their majority in the House, in fact, did not do so, and the Republicans picked up about 10 seats there.  Democrats expected to win the Senate, and they did not do so, and the Republicans held on to their majority there, or at least at the current count levels, that's what it looks like.
